# Development Plan
## Produce Ordering App — GoVigi Intern Assessment

**Total Timeline:** 3–4 Days  
**Stack:** Node.js · Express · MongoDB · Next.js · React Native (Expo)

---

## Day-by-Day Plan

### Day 1 — Backend Foundation

**Goal:** Fully working API with auth, products, and orders. Testable via Postman/curl.

Morning (3–4 hrs):
- Set up monorepo structure (`/backend`, `/web`, `/mobile`)
- Initialize Express app with `cors`, `dotenv`, `mongoose`
- Connect to MongoDB Atlas
- Create `User`, `Product`, `Order` Mongoose models

Afternoon (3–4 hrs):
- Implement `POST /api/auth/register` and `POST /api/auth/login` with bcrypt + JWT
- Implement Firebase Admin SDK integration and `POST /api/auth/firebase-login`
- Write `verifyJWT` middleware
- Implement `GET /api/products` (public)
- Implement `POST /api/orders` and `GET /api/orders` (protected)
- Write seed script with 5+ products (3 vegetables, 2+ fruits)
- Create `backend/.env.example`

End of Day 1 Checkpoint:
- [ ] All 5 API endpoints return correct status codes
- [ ] JWT auth works on protected routes
- [ ] Seed script populates DB successfully
- [ ] No secrets in code

---

### Day 2 — Next.js Web Portal

**Goal:** All 5 web pages functional, JWT stored, SSR working for products.

Morning (3–4 hrs):
- Initialize Next.js project in `/web`
- Set up Axios instance with JWT interceptor (`lib/api.js`)
- Build Login page and Register page (forms → API → store JWT in localStorage)
- Initialize Firebase Web SDK, add Google Sign-In button
- Build shared `Navbar` component

Afternoon (3–4 hrs):
- Build Products page with SSR (`getServerSideProps` → `GET /api/products`)
- Build `ProductCard` component
- Build Place Order page (product selector, quantity input, date picker → `POST /api/orders`)
- Build My Orders page (`GET /api/orders` → list with `StatusBadge`)
- Apply GoVigi-inspired UI: green (#2E7D32 / #4CAF50) + white + warm greys
- Create `web/.env.example`

End of Day 2 Checkpoint:
- [ ] Register → Login → Products → Place Order → My Orders flow works end-to-end
- [ ] SSR confirmed (view source shows product HTML)
- [ ] Google Sign-In works
- [ ] JWT persists across page refreshes

---

### Day 3 — React Native Mobile App

**Goal:** All 5 screens functional, category filtering, orders viewable.

Morning (3–4 hrs):
- Initialize Expo project in `/mobile`
- Set up React Navigation (Stack + Bottom Tab)
- Build Auth screens: Login, Register (AsyncStorage for JWT)
- Set up `AuthContext` for global auth state
- Set up Axios instance with token interceptor

Afternoon (3–4 hrs):
- Build Product List screen with category filter tabs (Veg / Fruit)
- Build Place Order screen (product picker, quantity, date picker)
- Build My Orders screen with status badges
- Apply consistent GoVigi-style theming
- Test on Android emulator and/or Expo Go
- Create `mobile/.env.example`

End of Day 3 Checkpoint:
- [ ] All screens navigate correctly
- [ ] Auth persists with AsyncStorage
- [ ] Orders placed on mobile appear in web My Orders (and vice versa)
- [ ] Google Sign-In works on mobile

---

### Day 4 — Polish, Testing & Submission

**Goal:** Project is reviewable, runnable, and submission-ready.

Morning (2–3 hrs):
- Write comprehensive `README.md` covering:
  - Prerequisites (Node, MongoDB, Firebase)
  - Step-by-step setup for each part
  - Environment variable explanations
  - How to seed the database
  - How to run all three apps
- Final pass on error handling (missing fields, invalid tokens, non-existent products)
- Remove all `console.log` debug statements
- Verify `.env.example` files are accurate

Afternoon (1–2 hrs):
- Final end-to-end smoke test: fresh clone → setup → register → order → check status
- Review code quality: consistent naming, no duplicated logic, no dead code
- Push clean commit history to GitHub
- Submit link to hr@govigi.com

